fter: str # A cursor indicating where to start retrieving the next page of results. Use this parameter to paginate forward. Not required for the initial request. For subsequent requests, use the start_cursor value returned in meta.cursor_pagination from the previous response. Works with limit, direction, and other supported query parameters. When specified, offset-based pagination (page) is ignored. Cannot be used in combination with the before parameter.}
@returns(200) {data: [map], meta: map{pagination: map{total: int, count: int, per_page: int, current_page: int, total_pages: int, links: map{previous: str, current: str, next: str}}, cursor_pagination: map{count: int, per_page: int, start_cursor: str, end_cursor: str, links: map{previous: str, current: str, next: str}}}} # List of `Metafield` objects.

